  "prompt": "What is the validity period of Non-Creamy OBC certificate?",
  "response": "The validity period of a Non-Creamy Layer (NCL) Other Backward Class (OBC) certificate generally varies depending on the guidelines established by the issuing authority, such as state governments or specific institutions in India. Typically, the validity period for an OBC NCL certificate is one financial year, which means it may need to be renewed annually to reflect any changes in the individual's income status.\n\nHowever, it is crucial to check the specific requirements and validity period as stipulated by the authority for which the certificate is being submitted, as some might have different criteria. Always verify with the relevant institution or authority to ensure compliance with their current policies regarding the validity and renewal of the certificate.",
